        <p>Doc-To-Help's existing macro-enabled DOTM&#160;template files have been replaced with macro-free DOTX templates. </p>
        <p>When you open a new DOTX&#160;template, you will not see the Doc-To-Help ribbon. This is because the functionality available in the ribbon is not necessary when editing a template<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineOnly"> (see <MadCap:xref href="#modes">Dynamic Add-In Modes</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. However, you will still have access to Doc-To-Help styles and variables. </p>
        <p class="OnlineOnly">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../D2H/Templates/About-Templates-Styles-D2H.htm">About Templates and Styles</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../D2H/Introduction/Steps/Upgrading-Old-Projects.htm">Upgrading Old [%=Other.Product%] Projects</MadCap:xref>.</p>
